PATCH: Update ShopStatistics overall payment computation method
The ShopStatistics class has been updated by replacing the overall() method with a direct overall payment calculation inside an array. The payment computation process takes into account the sum of 'PAID', 'UNPAID', 'REFUNDED', and 'CANCELLED' OrderPayments. This contributes to simplified and more efficient code management.

PATCH: Refactor shop statistics and accounting metrics computation
Rewritten ShopStatistics and AccountingMain classes to improve and abstract metrics computations. Changes include new helper methods for calculating metric values, using improved and simplified database queries, and improved code readability. The refactored classes allow for more maintainable and efficient code. Also, extended the status checks in the calculation by introducing metrics for 'REFUNDED', 'UNPAID' and 'CANCELLED' statuses.

PATCH: Update Email and Voucher controllers and email layout
Modified VoucherController to use simplified code by importing namespace of ShopVouchers directly. Updated DefaultEmail to carry author information and added method for avatar fetching. Adjusted email layout to display the message's author and their avatar.

PATCH: Remove "from" parameter from DefaultEmail constructor
The "from" attribute was removed from the DefaultEmail class constructor. This is aimed at streamlining the code implementation, since the "from" field isn't necessary - the authenticated user is always the one sending the email.

PATCH: Remove "messageFrom" from DefaultEmail class
The "messageFrom" attribute and its instances were removed from the DefaultEmail class and the SendEmail screen. This refactors aims to simplify the implementation since the "from" field is not necessary in this context, as it is always the authenticated user sending the email.
